"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-29-paris-2024-olympics-good-fight-plumptre-thumbs-up-super-falcons-display-vs-spain\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Ashleigh Plumptre has showered encomium on the Super Falcons despite the team's defeat to Spain.  The Super Falcons put up a resolute display against the world champions but ended up losing the game 1-0.  Barcelona Femeni star, Alexia Putellas scored the winning goal in the 86th minute.  Plumptre, who missed out of the Olympics due to injury, was full of praises for her teammates.  \\\"This team knows how to defend - sheesh!Good fight @NGSuper_Falcons - proud to watch,\\\" the Al-Ittihad of Saudi Arabia defender wrote on X.  The Super Falcons will take on Japan in their last group game on Wednesday.  Okon leaves Remo Stars for Rivers United  Transfer: Real reason I joined Fabregas at Como after leaving Man United - Varane  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"